title: New Zealand beats Australia by 24 runs to regain Chappell-Hadlee trophy
text:
Australia v New Zealand: Black Caps win Chappell-Hadlee trophy with 24-run win, Aussies lose top ranking Posted February 05, 2017 17:11:50 Map: New Zealand 
Australia have relinquished the Chappell-Hadlee trophy and number one ODI ranking, with Mitchell Starc unable to save his batsmen's blushes in a dramatic 24-run loss to New Zealand in Hamilton. 
The understrength tourists, who were minus Test squad members Steve Smith, David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Mitch Marsh and Matthew Wade, did well to restrict NZ to 9-281 on Sunday. 
Starc finished 29 not out as Australia were all out for 257, suffering a 2-0 series loss after Trent Boult claimed six wickets in front of a sold-out crowd at Seddon Park. 
More to come.
